# REST API base URL — required in production. The build bakes this
# value into the client bundle, so changing it requires a rebuild.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000

# Socket.IO endpoint. NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL is the canonical name and
# is what the Render dashboard / deployment guides use. The legacy
# NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL alias is still accepted by the resolver in
# src/lib/server-urls.ts. If neither is set, the resolver falls back
# to NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL (same origin), which is correct for any host
# that serves both REST and Socket.IO from the same domain.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:4000
# NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=http://localhost:4000

# Optional — Google sign-in is hidden when not set.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
